    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-vv40-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors have been assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed their required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted on the basis that ASTM F1717 prescribes a single standardized test configuration for regulatory submissions and the shortfall is bounded by the high equivalency of the validation scenario to the COU. The E/uval metric is below 1.96 for all primary QoIs and all percentage differences are within the 10% acceptance bound. The overall credibility package supports an Accepted decision for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw FEA modeling framework under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending.",
